I'm currently logged in as 'admin' which is a member of the confluence-administrators group.  When I place page restrictions on a particular page for another user, 'testuser', permissions for my user, 'admin', are also added to the same page.  This seems unnecessary since I'm already a confluence-administrator and can already do everything.  I am fixing permissions like this across every single page in my instance and it seems rather 'spammy' to see my username have rights on every single page I touch.

The improvement would be to have the automatic script check first to see if the current user is already the Space Admin or Confluence Admin before explicitly adding the admin to the page restrictions list.

I can't even remove myself via the UI to fix this.

